              <DefinitionShort>to become safe from danger by avoiding or escaping{N:001}</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to escape</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to avoid</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The meaning of this part of {S:04500200300034} is ‘to become free from the danger of being judged by God.’ ἵνα κατισχύσητε ἐκφυγεῖν ταῦτα πάντα τὰ μέλλοντα γίνεσθαι ‘in order that you may be able to escape all of these things that are going to happen’ {S:04202103600018}. In {S:04500200300034} and {S:04202103600018} {L:ἐκφεύγω&lt;SDBG:ἐκφεύγω:000000&gt;} should not be understood in the literal sense of running away from (see {D:15.63}). The meaning is simply not to become involved in such danger.</Comments>
